&lt;title&gt;Rapid Texture Identification&lt;/title&gt;

A method is presented for classifying each pixel of a textured image, and thus segmenting the scene. The "texture energy" approach requires only few convolutions with small (typically 5x5) integer coefficient masks, followed by moving-window absolute average operation. Normalization local mean standard deviation eliminates need histogram equalization. Rotation-invariance can also be achieved using averages texture energy features. convolution masks are separable, implemented 1-dimensional (vertical horizontal) or multipass 3x3 convolutions. Special techniques permit rapid processing on general-purpose digital computers.

